# Plugin DeployPlugin Target Pattern

## Rule

Every plugin project (`TorrentPlugin`, `SocialMediaPlugin`, `YoutubePlugin`, `DownloadPlugin`) MUST have a `DeployPlugin` MSBuild target that copies **all** DLLs from `$(OutputPath)` to the main app's `bin/Plugins/<Name>` folder — NOT just the plugin's own DLL.

## Why

`CopyLocalLockFileAssemblies=true` copies NuGet transitive dependencies (e.g. `MonoTorrent.Client.dll`, `Ytdlp.NET.dll`) to the plugin's own build output folder.  
If `DeployPlugin` only copies the plugin DLL by name, those NuGet DLLs are **not** deployed, and the app crashes at runtime with:

> Unable to load one or more of the requested types. Could not load file or assembly 'MonoTorrent.Client, ...'. The system cannot find the file specified.

## Correct Pattern

```xml
<Target Name="DeployPlugin" AfterTargets="Build">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <PluginsDir>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\..\TelegramAutoDownload\bin\$(Configuration)\net8.0-windows\Plugins\<FolderName></PluginsDir>
  </PropertyGroup>
  <ItemGroup>
    <!-- Wildcard: copies plugin DLL + ALL NuGet dependencies, excluding BasePlugins.dll (shared, already in app root) -->
    <PluginOutputDlls Include="$(OutputPath)*.dll" Exclude="$(OutputPath)BasePlugins.dll" />
  </ItemGroup>
  <MakeDir Directories="$(PluginsDir)" />
  <Copy SourceFiles="@(PluginOutputDlls)" DestinationFolder="$(PluginsDir)" SkipUnchangedFiles="true" />
</Target>
```

## Wrong Pattern (never do this)

```xml
<!-- BAD: only copies the plugin DLL, NuGet dependencies are missing -->
<Copy SourceFiles="$(OutputPath)TorrentPlugin.dll" DestinationFolder="$(PluginsDir)" />

<!-- BAD: hardcoding specific dependency names breaks when packages update -->
<Copy SourceFiles="$(OutputPath)Ytdlp.NET.dll" ... />
```

## After Modifying a Plugin

Always rebuild the plugin project explicitly before launching the app:

```powershell
dotnet build TorrentPlugin/TorrentPlugin.csproj -c Release --no-incremental
dotnet build SocialMediaPlugin/SocialMediaPlugin.csproj -c Release --no-incremental
dotnet build YoutubePlugin/YoutubePlugin.csproj -c Release --no-incremental
```

The main app project build (`TelegramAutoDownload.csproj`) does NOT trigger `DeployPlugin` on the plugin sub-projects because they are referenced with `ReferenceOutputAssembly="false"`.

## Publish Checklist

The `CopyPluginsToPublishDir` target in `TelegramAutoDownload.csproj` handles releases.  
For local dev runs, `DeployPlugin` in each plugin `.csproj` handles it.  
Both must use the wildcard `*.dll` pattern — never hardcode individual DLL names.
